column5: what is the status of highway 53 going through Duluth?

I went thru Duluth in early June on 53. The road to the top of the hill is all done, that is, to the old 5-way stop. From there on until you get out to the mall area is under construction but to my knowledge is still open. As long as the hill project took, I would expect this portion to drag on also. It's not all that big a deal. Some delays at the intersections. They did not have lights working, rather used stop signs. It's still quicker than the detour before the new road opened.
Yup, it's essentially done. We got through there around 1 pm in early June too w/o any problems.
Its no better/worse than it was previous years. The line is more straightshot now, however, expect about a 10 minute delay total - its not bad at all.

If you are coming from Superior and taking 53 through Duluth, that is awfully slow (in my opinion) as compared to hopping on 35 south to US-2. If you follow US-2 a little ways west, you hit, I believe 33 which is 4 lanes and that runs directly into 53 headed to I-Falls. Less lights, less traffice, less construction, less headache. May be worth it to try it sometime... Just a thought... Steve
